{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"reversed"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s18ReversedCollectionV","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/ReversedCollection","text":"ReversedCollection"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Self"},{"kind":"text","text":">"}]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can reverse a collection without allocating new space for its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"elements by calling this ","type":"text"},{"code":"reversed()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" method. A "},{"code":"ReversedCollection","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"instance wraps an underlying collection and provides access to its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"elements in reverse order. This example prints the characters of a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"string in reverse order:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let word = \"Backwards\"","for char in word.reversed() {","    print(char, terminator: \"\")","}","// Prints \"sdrawkcaB\""],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need a reversed collection of the same type, you may be able to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"use the collection’s sequence-based or collection-based initializer. For","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"example, to get the reversed version of a string, reverse its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"characters and initialize a new ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"String"},{"text":" instance from the result.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let reversedWord = String(word.reversed())","print(reversedWord)","// Prints \"sdrawkcaB\""],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"O(1)"}]}],"name":"Complexity"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String/UnicodeScalarView"]]},"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["/documentation/swift/string/unicodescalarview/reversed()"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/String/UnicodeScalarView/reversed()"},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"reversed()","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"externalID":"s:SKsE8reverseds18ReversedCollectionVyxGyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:SS17UnicodeScalarViewV","extendedModule":"Swift","roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"reversed","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ReversedCollection","preciseIdentifier":"s:s18ReversedCollectionV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"Self","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">","kind":"text"}]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Returns a view presenting the elements of the collection in reverse","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"order.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/ReversedCollection":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ReversedCollection"}],"title":"ReversedCollection","type":"topic","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/ReversedCollection","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A collection that presents the elements of its base collection"},{"typ